This paper proposes a non-negative risk estimator for PU learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper also mentions the use of deep neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The analysis of bias, consistency, and mean-squared-error reduction suggests a theoretical aspect, which could fall under the category of algorithms (cs.DS). Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
